## GDPR / Personvern

Hjelpi processes personal data of Norwegian residents. The following requirements are non-negotiable.

### Cookie consent

Use **Cookiebot** (configured via `COOKIEBOT_ID` env var). Load the Cookiebot script in the root layout before any analytics or tracking scripts:

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
<Script
  id="cookiebot"
  src="https://consent.cookiebot.com/uc.js"
  data-cbid={process.env.COOKIEBOT_ID}
  strategy="beforeInteractive"
/>
```

PostHog and Sentry must not initialise until Cookiebot fires the `CookiebotOnAccept` event. Never load analytics in `beforeInteractive` — only after consent.

Cookie categories:
- **Necessary:** Supabase auth session cookie — always active, no consent needed
- **Statistics:** PostHog — requires consent
- **Marketing:** none at launch

### Required pages

Every page links to these in the footer:
- `/no/personvern` — Privacy policy (who we are, what data, why, how long, rights)
- `/no/vilkar` — Terms of service
- `/no/cookie-policy` — Cookie details

These pages must be translated for every locale before that locale goes live.

### Data minimisation

- Only collect data you actually use. Don't store buyer's phone number unless they provide it.
- Provider images stored in R2 under `/providers/{provider_id}/` — never in a public, guessable path.
- Booking `cancellation_reason` is visible to admin only — not to the other party unless they're involved.

### User data rights (GDPR Articles 15–22)

All accessible from `/no/min-konto/innstillinger`:

**Export (Art. 15 / 20):** `GET /api/user/export`
Returns a JSON file of everything stored: profile, bookings, reviews, messages, notifications, saved providers.
```ts
// Must complete within 30 days of request. For large accounts, generate async and email a download link.
```

**Deletion (Art. 17):** `DELETE /api/user`
Two-phase:
1. Immediate: set `profiles.deleted_at = now()`, anonymise `full_name` to "Slettet bruker", clear `phone`, `avatar_url`. RLS now hides the profile from all queries.
2. Async (Trigger.dev job, runs within 30 days): delete `auth.users` record via service role, delete R2 files, delete Stripe customer data, remove from Typesense.

```ts
// Bookings are retained for accounting/legal purposes (7 years per Norwegian bokføringsloven)
// but are de-identified: buyer_id / provider references anonymised
```

**Correction (Art. 16):** Users can update their profile data at any time via `/no/min-konto/innstillinger`.

**Objection to processing (Art. 21):** Contact form — handled manually by Hjelpi team.

### Sub-processors

Hjelpi's privacy policy must list all sub-processors. Current list:
| Processor | Data shared | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Supabase (EU region) | All user & booking data | Database & auth |
| Stripe | Payment data, identity | Payments & payouts |
| Cloudflare R2 | Provider photos | File storage |
| Resend | Email address, name | Transactional email |
| PostHog (EU) | Anonymised analytics | Product analytics |
| Signicat/Criipto | Name, national ID number | BankID verification |
| Typesense | Provider public data | Search index |
| Trigger.dev | Job metadata | Background jobs |
| Vercel | IP address, request logs | Hosting |
| Sentry | Error traces (no PII in breadcrumbs) | Error monitoring |

**Never add a new sub-processor without updating the privacy policy first.**

### Data residency

All Supabase data must be in an EU region (Frankfurt or Stockholm). Verify in Supabase project settings before launch. PostHog must be on the EU cloud (`eu.posthog.com`).

### Retention periods

| Data | Retention |
|---|---|
| Active profiles | Until deletion request |
| Soft-deleted profiles | 30 days, then hard delete |
| Booking records | 7 years (Norwegian accounting law) |
| Payment records | 7 years |
| Messages | 2 years after booking completion |
| Notifications | 1 year |
| Analytics events | 1 year (PostHog setting) |
| Server logs (Vercel) | 30 days |

Trigger.dev jobs enforce these retention periods automatically. Add a scheduled job `cleanup-expired-data` that runs weekly.

